<TITLE> Help flood victims, Iajuddin urges at U21Global launch </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 13 (bdnews24.com) - President Iajuddin Ahmed Monday urged people to stand by one-third of Bangladeshis affected by floods. "I call upon all the countrymen to extend your cooperation for the well-being of the flood-affected people," Iajuddin said in his address as chief guest to the launch of U21Global, an online graduate school, at Dhaka Sheraton Hotel. Foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury also attended the opening ceremony as special guest. Co-organised by the U21Global and its local partner aiminlife.com, the inaugural ceremony started half an hour behind schedule at 11.34am. U21Global, having a network of 19 universities, offers certificate and master's courses on business management and information technology management. Chief executive of U21Global Dr Mukesh Aghi, chief adviser to aiminlife.com Syed Marghub Morshed, former FBCCI president Yusuf Abdullah Haroon, U21Global's dean Helen Lange and chief executive of aiminlife.com M Shoeb Chowdhury were also present. bdn
